The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during the signing of the National Defense Authorization Act. In his remarks, Trump praises the first responders and law enforcement for their response to the recent terrorist attack in New York City. He also emphasizes the need to end the visa lottery system and chain migration. Trump discusses the importance of the National Defense Authorization Act in rebuilding the military and ensuring readiness. He highlights the funding for the fight against ISIS and missile defense capabilities. Trump also mentions the increase in the size of the Armed Forces and a pay increase for military servicemembers. He urges Congress to eliminate the defense sequester and pass a clean appropriations bill to fully fund the military. Trump concludes by expressing his appreciation for the bipartisan support and thanking the military for their service.